hi I'm Kelsey from BT English today I'm
going to teach you ten acronyms that are
used in everyday English ASAP ASAP
stands for as soon as possible it can be
used in written English like in emails
or text or in spoken English you can
either say ASAP or ASAP
[Applause]
RSVP in English please RSVP as a way to
say respond when it comes to invitation
it's common to write or say please RSVP
by a certain date but it actually comes
from the French respond days people play
which means please respond n/a n/a means
not applicable this is often seen on
forums or questionnaires so when a
question doesn't apply to you you can
circle or write n/a
[Music]
aka aka stands for also known as it's
used to refer to another name for
someone or something PS PS means
PostScript which comes from the latin
post scriptum meaning written after it's
used to add a thought after an email or
letter has been completed dear Scott I
haven't been able to find you all day I
really miss you if you get this letter
give me a call from Kelsey PS you still
owe me five dollars ETA ETA stands for
estimated time of arrival it can be
written or spoken and is used to
indicate when someone or something will
arrive at a destination TBD
TVB means to be determined it's used
when something hasn't been decided on
yet but will be in the future all right
these are the details for annex feeding
fYI fYI stands for for your information
people often use this when forwarding an
email to someone as a way to quickly
tell them that this information might
relate to them you can also say FYI but
be careful because it can sometimes
sound rude
[Music]
TV a TV a means to be announced it's
used when something will be announced in
the future
[Music]
m-i-a m-i-a stands for missing in action
it was originally used to describe
soldiers that went missing during war
but today people also use it casually to
say that someone has disappeared
